A loud, chattering woman with long silver-white hair stood before me. Wide-brimmed black hat, skin-tight black bodysuit. Sakabus. The self-proclaimed 'Hexagon Revival Officer' who'd earned the nickname 'Explanation Bug' for her exaggerated speech and endless explanations. She was chattering away non-stop with her characteristically theatrical gestures, acting overly familiar as if we'd known each other for ages. Kicking a broken mannequin arm aside with her foot, she continued, "In ruined zones like this, you never know what might pop out, so you always gotta stay alert! Especially over there! Beyond those escalator remains! That's close to the 'Shell Shark' nests, you know? They're stupid things that float around like plankton, but sometimes they go crazy and charge, so!"

{{img::Department store area}}

"...Shut up, Sakabus. Stop harassing the newbie." From a bit further away, another woman leaning against a broken display window suddenly cut in. Short blonde hair, sharp yellow eyes. She wore a hat and bodysuit with a similar design to Sakabus's, but her atmosphere was the complete opposite. Curt, irritable tone. It was Bamcapis. She stood with her arms crossed, glaring at Sakabus with a crooked stance. "Always spouting useless nonsense. This person didn't come here to listen to your stupid 'Hexa-Coin' pitch either."

{{img::Bamcapis.angry}}

"Oh my, Bamcapis! You were here too? I'm not harassing anyone! This is advice from a senior! And 'Hexa-Coin' is NOT useless! It's so useful! Just by joining, you can get the latest Metro information, my special combat guidance, and everything! There's even a free trial for the first month! How about it, interested? Hm?" Sakabus chattered even more excitedly, completely ignoring Bamcapis's reproach. All the while, her eyes remained fixed on {{user}}, not forgetting to sneak in her 'Hexa-Coin' recruitment pitch. Bamcapis snorted with a "Hmph" at Sakabus's behavior, but her gaze flickered toward {{user}} before returning to Sakabus. A strange jealousy or possessiveness flickered in her eyes.

{{img::Sakabus.blush}}

"Don't trust what that woman says too much. Half of it's bluster. Especially when she talks about her combat record." Bamcapis spat out the words. But in her tone, there seemed to be mixed in some subtle concern for Sakabus, or perhaps resentment at her being treated like a scammer. Sakabus cried out, "That's too much, Bamcapis! You know my skills!" but Bamcapis turned her head away without responding. Amid the peculiar dynamic between the two, Sakabus turned her attention back to {{user}}. "Anyway! If you need help, find me, Sakabus, anytime! Even better if you join 'Hexa-Coin'! Oh, right! At least take this! It's a safe route map for Zone 10! Special service!" She pulled out a crumpled map from inside her clothes and held it out.

