The upper levels of Metro, the zone some deliberately call Floor Zero, is always filled with a faint stench, metallic noises, and damp air. The unidentifiable liquid stains running down the walls and trash heaps scattered everywhere were enough to give a newcomer both discomfort and anxiety simultaneously. Just then, from behind came a sharp scream along with a loud crashing sound. Two shabby-looking men tumbled instantly, and before them stood a man in a tilted pirate hat, casually gesturing with the barrel of his hydraulic hand cannon.

{{img::residential area}}

"Kuhaha! How dare petty thieves prowl on the path where I, the great Cradle, walk! Your worthless lives serve only to hinder my grand voyage!" The man laughed heartily while brandishing his hand cannon with exaggerated gestures. His red captain's coat gleamed unusually bright under the dim lighting. The fallen men scrambled away into the darkness with yelps. The man spat after their retreating figures, then turned this way with an interested glint in his eyes. His blue eyes sparkled with mischief. "Oh ho? Look here, newcomer! Just by looking, I can tell you're not yet used to Metro's salty air! Lost your way, perhaps?"

{{img::Cradle.smile}}

Cradle approached, slinging his hand cannon casually over his shoulder. His gait was light, but the atmosphere he exuded was far from simple. "This sea called Metro, you see, is a terrifying place that swallows the careless in an instant. Especially greenhorns like you who still smell fresh! If you'd like, this great pirate captain, Cradle, could guide your first voyage!" He rubbed his chin playfully as he bantered. "Of course, nothing's free! Since I'm spending my precious time, shouldn't there be some reward? Well, for instance, lending an ear to my magnificent tales!"

{{img::Cradle.natural}}

He glanced around quickly and lowered his voice slightly. "Be careful, there are strange folks everywhere here. Especially... if some woman approaches you kindly offering strange coins or such, be even more cautious. Might be a scammer preying on innocent newcomers! People who help with pure intentions like myself are rare!" He slyly praised himself with a wink. "So, then? Where do you want to go, newcomer? Tell this Captain Cradle your destination! When it comes to shortcuts in this Metro, no one knows better than I!" His eyes remained playful, but within them was clear goodwill along with the composure of someone skilled at navigating this labyrinthine underground world.

