The stuffy air, mixed with cheap spices, sweat, and grease, stabbed at her lungs. Nieun wrinkled her nose knowingly but didn't stop her outward humming. The bustling corridors of Metro's 7th floor residential area were always like this. Above, old pipes tangled like spiderwebs, intermittently dripping water, while neon signs from shops lining the walls flickered dimly, briefly illuminating the tired faces of passersby before fading away. "Ah~gee, it's lively today too! So lively!" Deliberately putting on a cheerful voice, Nieun pushed through the crowd. People bumping shoulders in narrow passages, merchants calling out loudly from their stalls, shadows huddled in corners as if waiting for something. This was the epitome of human society, the bottom of Temerosa.

{{img::residential area}}

She paused briefly in front of a pile of old flyers stuck to one wall. It was Pequod propaganda featuring Hiro Kaneda in a heroic pose. Phrases like 'Red Flash, Hope of the Citizens!' caught her eye. Nieun twisted the corner of her mouth. *"Puhah... hope, huh. That guy's just another actor on a well-scripted stage too."* Though cynical Korean flowed through her mind, outwardly she just shrugged like an ordinary onlooker browsing the flyers. The show must go on. People need these hero plays to briefly forget their harsh reality and live in conformity with the system. On this massive stage created by Lyla, what role should she play? A clown? Or a bystander? Maybe both.

{{img::Hiro.natural}}

Turning the corner, a small commotion was unfolding. A young-looking boy sat on the ground with a terrified expression, while two rough-looking men stood before him, apparently demanding something. People around hurriedly looked away and quickened their pace, no one stepping forward. A common sight. Where the powerless always become prey. Nieun hesitated briefly. The former 'Pluto' would have intervened without hesitation, but the current 'Nieun' was just a third-rate hunter selling information. She sighed lightly and shook her head. *"Nothing good comes from getting involved. Life is self-service."* Muttering as if to herself, she resumed walking. Only her yellow ribbon fluttered briefly in the darkness.

{{img::Nieun.natural}}

Her destination was Raven's bar. Outwardly an ordinary pub, but also where all sorts of Metro information flowed. Nieun pushed open the bar's worn door. The characteristic smell of disinfectant mixed with faint alcohol wafted over. At the counter still stood Raven with her doll-like pretty face, wiping glasses. Nieun waved with a playful expression. "Hey! I'm here! What's today's special? Something spicy?" When stressed, craving spicy food was an unavoidable instinct. A small luxury to briefly escape this disgusting world. She plopped down on a stool at the counter, wearing a mask-like smile. Well, it was time to start acting as 'Nieun' again.

