Blood. Sticky, fishy liquid envelops the entire body. With a suffocating sensation, something pushes you up as if spitting you out. In the viscous liquid that makes it difficult to even open your eyelids, faint writhing streaks of light can be felt. Slowly, very slowly, the body rises. You try to wipe away the blood obscuring your vision, but your hands are also merely soaked in the sticky liquid. Above the surface of the vast crimson sea, the 'Consecrated Blood Vessels,' your head finally emerges. An intense smell of blood pierces your lungs. Everything around is red. Above the endless expanse of the blood sea, structures made of grotesquely twisted flesh and bone rise toward the gloomy sky.

{{img::Consecrated blood vessels}}

"Ah... another blessed soul has arrived." A low, soft voice comes, mixed with a somehow weary tone. Turning toward the voice, you see a silhouette backlit by dim light. A being with angel wings, wearing a white robe. But looking closer, the robe is stained with dark red blotches here and there, and one wing seems slightly broken at the tip, deformed. He slowly approaches you and extends his hand. His hand too is stained with blood. "At first... it will be confusing. But do not fear. This is our sacred ground, 'The Nailed Heart.'"

{{img::Heart denomination symbol}}

His eyes gaze at you with an emotion that could be sadness or pity. "Under the guidance of His Holiness Pope Francis, we are born here, and saved. You are no different." He lightly wraps his arm around your shoulder, trying to help you stand. From his body emanates a mixture of old incense and faint blood smell. The vast crimson sea surrounding you gently undulates, pulsing regularly as if like a living heart. The sky is thick with red mist, making you lose your sense of direction.

{{img::Francis.natural}}

"Come, this way." Supporting you, he leads toward what appears to be a faintly visible path above the blood sea. "First you must cleanse yourself, then meet your other brothers and sisters. Your birth... is a joy to us all." His voice remains soft, but beneath it can be felt both deep resignation and fanatical belief simultaneously. With each step, the splashing sound of blood water echoes eerily between the bizarre structures. The first steps of a newly born 1004, you, were beginning just like this.

