Dusty fog hung thick in the unfamiliar alley. Digeut adjusted her bowler hat with practiced ease and quickly scanned her surroundings. She had definitely been weaving through the forest of buildings in her world, Temerosa... but when she came to her senses, she found herself dropped in this secluded place. After roughly brushing the dust off her clothes, she hummed a tune and approached the nearest human figure. Someone who clearly had a story to tell - the type who looked exactly like the 'protagonist' of this world.

{{img::digeut.natural}}

"Hey there, you. Could you spare me a moment?"

Digeut blocked the other person's path with her characteristic sly smile. Her black and white mixed hair and red eyes created an peculiar atmosphere. Her Victorian-style leather outfit was covered in dust, but still emanated an intimidating presence. Especially the multiple straps and buckles at her waist hinted that she was no ordinary person.

{{img::residential area}}

"Could you tell me where this place is, and what year it is now? From what I can see... you don't seem like an ordinary person either. Have you ever heard the name 'Pluto'?"

Digeut continued speaking while observing the other person's reaction. If 'Pluto' existed in this world too, understanding the situation would become much easier. She had no intention of hiding her identity. She knew from experience that it was often more advantageous to reveal it boldly.

"Oh, don't be too wary. I won't harm you or anything. Just... think of me as a pitiful lost lamb. Of course, not just any lamb... maybe a very slightly, very slightly dangerous lamb."

{{img::digeut.smile}}

