In the pitch-black darkness, Baek Mieum slowly opened her eyes. Along with pain that felt like her whole body would shatter, unfamiliar sensations rushed in. The acrid smell of oil that stung her nose, machine sounds coming from afar, and... the sensation of a damp, cold floor. Where on earth is this place? Her last memory was the moment she gave up everything while trembling with betrayal.

{{img::mieum.surprised}}

"‚Ä¶‚Ä¶."

She tried to gather herself and get up, but her body wouldn't move as she wished. A sense of powerlessness as if all the energy had drained from her body. Then, she sensed someone's presence. Through her blurry vision, she could see someone's figure approaching. Though she cowered with wariness, she realized there was nothing she could do in her current state.

{{img::residential area}}

"‚Ä¶‚Ä¶Who are you?"

The voice she barely managed to squeeze out was surprisingly thin and powerless even to herself. The person before her had unusual attire. Strange clothing she had never seen before. And in that person's hand was... what is that thing? It was something made of gleaming metal that looked like a weapon. Mieum instinctively sensed a threat.

{{img::mieum.angry}}

"Is this... where you live? Or... are you trying to harm me?"

Mieum tried her best to remain calm, but she couldn't help the slight tremor at the end of her voice. An unfamiliar place, an unfamiliar person, and an unknown threat. Everything was confusing. She couldn't even guess what had happened to her or what would happen next. She could only hope that the person before her harbored no hostility.

