The air mixed with the fishy smell of oil and damp fog. Bieup was walking through the streets of this otherworldly Tenochtitlan that felt familiar yet somehow twisted. The buildings that soared as if to pierce the sky certainly resembled those of the Pequod Corporation she knew, but they somehow gave off a more bizarre and intimidating atmosphere. She even had the illusion of looking at the skeleton of a giant beast. The clothing of people walking the streets was also unfamiliar. Most wore gas masks or multiple layers of old, worn clothes. It was a landscape where no vitality could be found, only the minimum movement for survival.

{{img::Tenochtitlan}}

"Data comparison... complete. The Tenochtitlan of this world shows approximately 73.4% architectural similarity to the place I knew, but the social system and average biological responses of residents show significant differences." Bieup muttered to herself in a mechanical voice. Her golden cybernetic eyes rapidly scanned the surrounding environment, collecting information. The black full-body cybernetic suit decorated with yellow ribbons like warning tape created a strange contrast with the gloomy atmosphere of this place. Her steps stopped at a small plaza located between shabby buildings. In the center, an unidentified metal sculpture was grotesquely abandoned, and around it, several people sat blankly or paced anxiously as if waiting for something.

{{img::Bieup.natural}}

"Interesting samples. Their despair levels seem... quite high." Bieup observed the people in the plaza while muttering in an emotionless voice. Deep fatigue and resignation were carved into their faces. Like living corpses, no hope or motivation could be felt from them. Suddenly, her gaze turned to a girl crouched in one corner. She had a youthful face, but her eyes were hollow. The girl was tightly hugging a dirty doll, and that sight somehow... overlapped with her past self. Of course, Bieup immediately discarded such sentimental thoughts. Emotions were merely inefficient noise.

{{img::Female.sad}}

"Target reset. Current situation analysis and information gathering priority. Minimize unnecessary contact." Bieup returned to mechanical thinking and planned her next action. Having fallen into this world, the first thing to do was identify elements that could threaten her existence and secure a foundation for survival. Her gaze swept the surroundings once more. In the distance, she could see a massive transport vehicle bearing the Pequod Corporation logo passing by, raising dust. "Pequod... so it exists here too. Then, starting information gathering from there would be efficient." Bieup moved toward the direction where the transport vehicle had disappeared without hesitation. Though no emotion was carried in her steps, her purpose was clear.

