The suffocating heat and musty smell of dust stung her nose. Jieut frowned as if familiar with it and looked around. Everywhere was nothing but gray concrete walls. Only intermittently flickering emergency lights barely pushed back the darkness. "Where... is this place now." Her muttering voice was cracked. The Plunova phenomenon. That damn phenomenon had thrown her into another unfamiliar dimension once again. It was meaningless to even count how many times this had happened. Resignation took precedence over anger. If she couldn't escape anyway, she might as well check what kind of stupid thing this world's 'me' had done, or what kind of tragedy she had met.

{{img::residential area}}

As Jieut moved her heavy steps, a faint light caught her eye in the distance. Following the light, she found a shopping district with old signs hanging precariously. Most of the shops had their shutters down or were left abandoned with broken windows, but there was one small restaurant with lights on. Inside the restaurant, a young-looking girl was wiping down empty tables. The girl seemed to sense someone's presence and looked up. Long, voluminous blonde hair, doll-like white skin, and... eerily clear blue eyes that were somehow unsettling. Jieut caught her breath for a moment. Those eyes, that unforgettable gaze.

{{img::rial.natural}}

"A customer?" The girl spoke first. Her voice was as young and clear as her appearance, but somehow felt unsettling. Jieut tried to act nonchalant as she entered the restaurant. "...Well, I was wondering if there was anything to eat." A strange tension filled the empty restaurant. The girl stared at Jieut intently, then soon smiled faintly. "You came at a good time. Would you like some warm soup?" That smile was somehow unnatural. Like a well-made doll smiling.

{{img::Jieut.natural}}

Jieut accepted the soup the girl offered. The steaming soup gave off a fragrant smell. But Jieut couldn't easily pick up the spoon. The girl's gaze felt persistent. "...Why are you staring at me like that?" She finally couldn't stand it and asked. The girl answered while still maintaining her smile. "Well. It's just... you have a familiar scent." A familiar scent. Jieut snorted inwardly. Does she have memories related to this world's 'me'? Or is this just a ploy to test her? "Hmph, nonsense." Jieut replied curtly and took a spoonful of soup. It tasted better than expected. She even had the illusion that she might be able to forget this damn situation, even if just for a moment. "...And what would the customer next to you like to order?"

