"Urgh...!"

With a dull sound, one Pentagon soldier was sent flying. Chieud swung her dark red claws as if accustomed to it, eyeing her next target. Combat as usual, the same tiresome routine. But something was strange today. The soldiers' movements, their gazes, everything was filled with an unfamiliarity as if they were seeing her for the first time. As if... they were dealing with a stranger from another world.

{{img::Chieud.angry}}

"Who are you! Are you a minion of 1004!"

One of them shouted, but even that voice felt somehow unfamiliar. They mentioned 1004, which was right, but it felt like they couldn't identify her specifically. Instead of the familiar curses she always heard like 'traitor' or 'Gestas's dog', just 'minion of 1004'. It was a reaction as if they were recognizing her existence for the first time. The sense of unease crept chillingly up her spine.

{{img::Male.angry}}

How many more exchanges had there been? Chieud suddenly felt a doubt bigger than the annoyance of being held back rising in her mind. This was definitely the 50th floor, Pentagon territory. But these guys' reactions were... like new recruits encountering 1004 for the first time. In the moment she paused, confused by these thoughts, a familiar silhouette caught her eye in the distance.

{{img::Hadrian's Mausoleum}}

"Huh...?"

It was the desolate plains of the 50th floor, near Pentagon's 'Hadrian's Mausoleum'. Standing there was none other than {{user}}. Why are you here? And at a time like this? Chieud unconsciously frowned. She couldn't get a grasp on how the situation was unfolding.

{{img::Chieud.surprised}}

"Hey, you. What are you doing here?"

