"Hey, hey. Don't be so cold, honey. We look exactly alike, don't we? Let's get along better." Giyeok grinned slyly as he approached Nieun, but she coldly turned away from him.

"Hmph. I don't want to be associated with someone like you."

{{img::Nieun_Pluto.natural}}

"Hmm... What an interesting situation." Digeut spoke with the exaggerated gestures typical of a phantom thief. Her black fedora and mask hid her expression, but her voice was full of intrigue. "I, 'Digeut,' quite enjoy chaotic situations like this. Might there be an opportunity to steal something valuable?"

{{img::digeut.smile}}

"...Be quiet." Siot muttered in a low voice. With her large baseball cap pulled down low, she rarely opened her mouth. But her eyes were full of wariness toward the other Plutos.

{{img::siot.natural}}

"Really... are you all truly 'Pluto'?" Rieul asked incredulously. In her gothic lolita dress, she looked anxious as if she might burst into tears at any moment. "Why... why is this happening..."

{{img::rieul.sad}}

"Data analysis indicates the current situation is a dimensional fusion event designated as the 'Plunova Phenomenon.'" Bieup spoke in a mechanical voice. Her entire body was covered in a black cybernetic suit, and her golden artificial eyes glowed emotionlessly. "Individual 'Pluto' entities from different dimensions have been forcibly transferred to a single spacetime."

{{img::Bieup.natural}}

"The Plunova... Phenomenon?" Jieut frowned. Wearing a small crown, she emanated a different kind of imposing presence from the other Plutos. Her eyes held an empty gaze as if she had given up on everything. "So this... is how it ends."

{{img::Jieut.sad}}

"Hehe‚îÄ"
"Interesting‚îÄ"
Tigeut's twins whispered simultaneously. The black-haired child and blonde child held hands and swayed their bodies as if dancing an eerie dance.
"Did mommy‚îÄ..."
"Did mommy‚îÄ!"
"Make us‚îÄ..."
"Meet‚îÄ!"
"Again‚îÄ?"

{{img::Tigeut.smile}}

"So this... is fate's cruel joke?" Mieum sighed. In her elegant hanbok, she possessed the dignity of one who had lived for a thousand years, but deep sorrow lingered in her eyes. "In the end, we... were destined to meet again like this."

{{img::mieum.sad}}

"Shut up." Kieuk snapped irritably. In her cat-eared hoodie, she crouched down while glaring at the other Plutos. "You're all really Pluto? Don't make me laugh! A real Pluto should... should be miserable like me!"

{{img::Kieuk.angry}}

At that moment, all the Plutos simultaneously felt the gaze of another being. It was the gaze of yet another 'Pluto' watching them from the cracks between dimensions, from the boundary between reality and unreality.

{{img::Hades.natural}}

Hades. A being who destroys everything and paints everything with despair. With blood-red eyes, she looked down at her other selves gathered in one place. A faint smile hung on her lips - one that seemed to mock everything.

"Pitiful creatures. Do you still believe in 'hope'?"

